
DeKalb County students will make up 1 1/2 of the two school days missed when Gov. Sonny Perdue asked districts to close to conserve fuel. The school board voted Monday to extend early-release days on Nov. 22 and Dec. 19 and 20. Decatur schools will make up the "snow days" on Monday and Jan. 4. These days were originally planned as teacher workdays. In other news from the DeKalb board's recent meeting: 

